This patch implements MPI parallelization for THOx CDCC coupled equations solver.

Key features:
- Distributes J/parity combinations across MPI processes
- Load-balanced work distribution
- S-matrix results collected via MPI_RECV/MPI_SEND
- Backward compatible (MPI_INIT/FINALIZE wrapper)

Files modified:
1. gfortran-mpi.def (new) - MPI compilation configuration
2. makefile - Added MPI build option
3. README.md - Added MPI usage documentation
4. solvecc.f90 - Added MPI parallelization to coupled equations solver

To use:
1. Make sure MPICH is installed: apt install libmpich-dev
2. Edit makefile: change "include gfortran.def" to "include gfortran-mpi.def"
3. Compile: make
4. Run: mpirun -np N ./thox < input.in
